
Reference paper:
Huang, W., & Zhang, K. (2016). An information-Theoretic Framework for Fast and Robust Unsupervised Learning via neural population infomax. ICLR 2017, arXiv preprint arXiv:1611.01886. https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.01886

Instructions for running:
---------------------------------------------------------------------

You will first need to download image datasets 
to the folder: /HieInfomax/data, and run 'SaveMNIST2MAT' to save files 
of the raw MNIST images as '*.mat' format. Then you can run 'Main' for your tests.

Olshausen's raw (unwhitened) images are available from 
http://redwood.berkeley.edu/bruno/sparsenet/.

The handwritten digits of MNIST database are available from 
http://yann.lecun.com/exdb/mnist/.


